         <abstract>
            <p>A systematic method is given for calculating sets of $n$ squares of which any $n - 1$ have their sum square. A particular method is developed for $n = 4$. Tables give the smallest solution for each $n \leqslant 8$ and other small solutions for $n \leqslant 5$.</p>
